answers.body_markdown:
I found the solution, it was something simple I had to add `@Autowired` to **AuthenticationFailureHandler** and also to **AuthenticationSuccessHandler** and now it accomplishes the task.

    @Component
    public class AuthenticationFailureHandler extends SimpleUrlAuthenticationFailureHandler  {
    	
    	@Autowired
    	private SessionService service;
    	
    	@Override
    	public void onAuthenticationFailure(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response,
    			AuthenticationException exception) throws IOException, ServletException {
    		System.out.println(&quot;A user has falied to login. Error: &quot; + exception.getMessage());
    		
    		String ipAddress = request.getRemoteAddr();
    		
    		service.errorSession(ipAddress);
    		
    		super.setDefaultFailureUrl(&quot;/login?error&quot;);
    		super.onAuthenticationFailure(request, response, exception);
    		
    	}
    
    }

